        "confidence": "medium",
        "title": "Some constants are flagged extrapolations"
      },
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Not every pixel value in the analysis corpus is a direct measurement off the reference recordings. Some are documented extrapolations for states the source recordings didn't capture — for example, the "
        },
        {
          "insert": "SelectionToolbar",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " \"multi\" selection variant discussed in "
        },
        {
          "insert": "canvas-60-chrome",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true,
            "reference": {
              "kind": "doc",
              "path": "20-implementation/60-chrome",
              "label": "canvas-60-chrome"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": ", where the recordings never showed a multi-object selection long enough to sample cleanly. Treat any such extrapolated constant as a best guess, not ground truth, and reconfirm it against live FigJam before relying on it for a pixel-exact decision."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-appendix-heading-testing-15": {
