    "b-appendix-testing-block-17": {
      "id": "b-appendix-testing-block-17",
      "flavour": "testing",
      "props": {
        "title": "Unit tests for logic, DOM/geometry assertions for rendering — never screenshots"
      },
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Pure logic layers — "
        },
        {
          "insert": "state/",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": ", "
        },
        {
          "insert": "interaction/",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": ", "
        },
        {
          "insert": "connectors/",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " — get plain unit tests: given inputs, assert outputs, no rendering involved. The "
        },
        {
          "insert": "stage/",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " and "
        },
        {
          "insert": "stage/editor/",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " layers instead get happy-dom DOM and geometry assertion tests — checking computed styles, element positions, class names, and attribute values against expectations derived from "
        },
        {
          "insert": "board-design-reference/",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " — rather than visual screenshot/snapshot-image tests. This \"no screenshots\" philosophy was established for the chrome components (see "
        },
        {
          "insert": "canvas-60-chrome",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true,
            "reference": {
              "kind": "doc",
              "path": "20-implementation/60-chrome",
              "label": "canvas-60-chrome"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": ") and carried through the rest of the package: assertions are made on concrete, diffable values (a computed pixel width, a hex color, a DOM attribute) rather than on rendered pixels, so failures are legible and don't require a human to eyeball an image diff. The DOM-equivalence gate in "
        },
        {
          "insert": "zz-dom-equivalence.test.tsx",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true,
            "reference": {
              "kind": "source",
              "path": "packages/canvas/src/zz-dom-equivalence.test.tsx"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " and "
        },
        {
          "insert": "zz-dom-fixtures.ts",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true,
            "reference": {
              "kind": "source",
              "path": "packages/canvas/src/zz-dom-fixtures.ts"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " re-renders a fixed corpus (repo fixtures plus synthetic docs, three prop profiles each) and compares it against "
        },
        {
          "insert": "packages/canvas/zz-dom-baseline.json",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true,
            "reference": {
              "kind": "source",
              "path": "packages/canvas/zz-dom-baseline.json"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": ": HTML outside the style block must be byte-identical, the style block is compared structurally, and adversarial docs are reported but never auto-fail. The capture script is "
        },
        {
          "insert": "packages/canvas/zz-dom-capture.ts",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true,
            "reference": {
              "kind": "source",
              "path": "packages/canvas/zz-dom-capture.ts"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": ". It was the layout overhaul's DOM gate and stays active pending the registry refactor's retirement decision. The suite is deliberately red at HEAD: a frozen set of 6 failures (as of 2026-07-10 — the zz-dom baseline, the outline-anchor cascade baseline, three v2-flow fixture-parity assertions, and one below-slot text fixture) is kept byte-stable as a drift detector while overhaul work is in flight. The policy is prune, never regenerate: fixing a failure means updating the test or pruning the stale baseline entry, not re-capturing a green baseline over unexplained drift. \"Suite green\" is therefore not a gate in this repo; \"failure set identical\" is."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
